@{
	ViewBag.Title = "ConnectLocal";
	ViewBag.Message = "Get Local using Connect !!";
}

<hgroup class="title">
	<h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
</hgroup>

<article>
@section featured {
	<section class="featured">
		<div class="content-wrapper">
			<hgroup class="title">
				<h1>@ViewBag.Title.</h1>
				<h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
			</hgroup>
			<p>
				ConnectLocal is your gateaway to view local information about your destination before you get there.
			</p>
			<p>
				To learn more about Connect Platform visit
				<a href="https://developer.concur.com/" title="Concur Connect">https://developer.concur.com/</a>.
				The page features <mark>videos, tutorials, and samples</mark> to help you get the most from Concur Connect Platform.
				If you have any questions about Connect Platform contact
				<a href="https://developer.concur.com/en-us/support" title="Connect Support">our support team</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
}

<h3>We suggest the following:</h3>
<ol class="round">
	<li class="one">
		<h5>Getting Started</h5>
		Register for a free ConnectLocal account and link it your Sandbox account. If you do not have a Concur Sandbox you can get one <a href="https://developer.concur.com/register">here</a>. See how the use of Connect Platform and API allows you to use the traveler's trips and information.
		<a href="https://developer.concur.com/api-documentation/web-services/itinerary">Learn more…</a>
	</li>

	<li class="two">
		<h5>Review sample code</h5>
		This application provides sample code using github to demonstrate how to build your own applications using Connect API. The APIs used in this sample are - Itinerary, Travel Profile and ExpenseCapture. The sample code is available <a href="https://github.com/amolkasbekar/ConnectLocal">here</a> on github. This code here is meant only as a guidance and is not meant to use as-is.
	</li>

	<li class="three">
		<h5>Questions</h5>
		For questions regarding this app or the code on github, contact <a href="mailto:amol.kasbekar@concur.com">Amol Kasbekar</a>. For all other generic questions please contact <a href="https://developer.concur.com/en-us/support">Connect support</a> team.
	</li>
</ol>
</article>

<aside>
	<ul>
		<li>@Html.ActionLink("Home", "Index", "Home")</li>
		<li>@Html.ActionLink("About", "About", "Home")</li>
		<li>@Html.ActionLink("Contact", "Contact", "Home")</li>
		<li>@Html.ActionLink("Your Account", "Manage", "Home")</li>
	</ul>
</aside>